				 Bengal sees software export surge 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Hyderabad, Nov. 28: Bengal IT minister Debesh Das said he expected the state to occupy the third spot in software exports by 2010 from the current sixth position.																								Das said a chip design centre was coming up in Calcutta, and an IT park was being set up near Kharagpur.																								These facilities would attract more investments to the state.																								Speaking to journalists at INFOCOM 2007 here, Das said there were also plans to set up a venture capital company which will have an initial corpus of Rs 2 crore. 																								This will be scaled up to Rs 17 crore in the future.																								Das said that Videocon would set up their fab facility in the state at an investment of Rs 4,000 crore.																								He said land cost in the state was high because of higher compensation to farmers.																								R. Damodar Reddy, Das counterpart in Andhra Pradesh, said the state contributed to around 14 per cent of Indias software exports.																								He said the state government planned to offer employment to 10 lakh people in the IT sector. 
